{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AuVuj96quagXJRYV6yQYbj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.addressbookspring.service;\n     2→\n     3→import com.example.addressbookspring.entity.Contact;\n     4→import com.example.addressbookspring.repo.ContactRepository;\n     5→import org.springframework.data.domain.PageRequest;\n     6→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n     7→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Service\n    12→@Transactional\n    13→public class ContactService {\n    14→    private final ContactRepository repo;\n    15→\n    16→    public ContactService(ContactRepository repo) {\n    17→        this.repo = repo;\n    18→    }\n    19→\n    20→\n    21→    public void create(Contact entity) {\n    22→        repo.save(entity); \n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    public void edit(Contact entity) {\n    26→        repo.save(entity); \n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    public void remove(Contact entity) {\n    30→        if (entity == null) return;\n    31→        Long id = entity.getId();\n    32→        if (id != null && repo.existsById(id)) {\n    33→            repo.deleteById(id);\n    34→        } else {\n    35→            repo.delete(entity); \n    36→        }\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    public Contact find(Long id) {\n    40→        return (id == null) ? null : repo.findById(id).orElse(null);\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    public List<Contact> findAll() {\n    44→        return repo.findAll();\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    public List<Contact> findRange(int[] range) {\n    48→        int start = range[0];\n    49→        int endExclusive = range[1];\n    50→        int size = Math.max(0, endExclusive - start);\n    51→        if (size <= 0) return List.of();\n    52→        int page = start / size;\n    53→        return repo.findAll(PageRequest.of(page, size)).getContent();\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    public int count() {\n    57→        long c = repo.count();\n    58→        return (c > Integer.MAX_VALUE) ? Integer.MAX_VALUE : (int) c;\n    59→    }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NtZdmfJPW3RpmTYySMgiUg","session_id":"d72ec4a1-bfc7-4aa5-bf05-2da291fff045","uuid":"ae306cc7-c408-481d-abce-d49c4cca0ebe"}
