{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012jeVMMQ7YFyNBJ8fvCQKAj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<faces-config xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\"\n     3→              xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     4→              xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\n     5→              https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-facesconfig_4_0.xsd\"\n     6→              version=\"4.0\">\n     7→\n     8→    <application>\n     9→        <resource-bundle>\n    10→            <base-name>Bundle</base-name>\n    11→            <var>bundle</var>\n    12→        </resource-bundle>\n    13→    </application>\n    14→\n    15→</faces-config>\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NtZdmfJPW3RpmTYySMgiUg","session_id":"d72ec4a1-bfc7-4aa5-bf05-2da291fff045","uuid":"c0265e7f-955d-455c-9037-cd42e634f061"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NtZdmfJPW3RpmTYySMgiUg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Other Notable Files:\n- `.dockerignore`\n- `mvnw`\n- `mvnw.cmd`\n\nSummary of the Spring Address Book Application:\n\n1. Architecture:\n- Spring Boot application with JPA and JSF\n- Uses H2 in-memory database\n- Implements a Contact management system\n- Uses Jakarta EE (formerly Java EE) technologies\n\n2. Key Components:\n- `Contact` entity: Represents contact information with validation\n- `ContactRepository`: Spring Data JPA repository \n- `ContactService`: Service layer for business logic\n- `ContactController`: JSF-based web controller for CRUD operations\n\n3. Configuration:\n- Uses Spring Boot auto-configuration\n- H2 in-memory database\n- JSF configured with JoinFaces\n- Application running on port 8080\n\n4. Features:\n- Create, Read, Update, Delete (CRUD) operations for contacts\n- Pagination support\n- Basic validation (email, phone number, date)\n- Resource bundling for internationalization\n\nThe application is a typical Spring Boot web application with JSF for the frontend, demonstrating standard enterprise Java web application patterns.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the codebase?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d72ec4a1-bfc7-4aa5-bf05-2da291fff045","uuid":"f37c9d0e-cdf3-4949-a083-874cad9701e9"}
